title: Practical Guide to Hydrogenated Nitrile Butadiene Rubber Technol
description:
Practical Guide to Hydrogenated Nitrile Butadiene Rubber Technology - Robert Keller (Smithers Rapra Technology, 2012).pdf

ISBN: 978-1-84735-521-8

Hydrogenated Nitrile Butadiene Rubber (HNBR) is a synthetic polymer that results from the hydrogenation of Nitrile Rubber (NBR). It is widely known for its physical strength and retention of properties after long-term exposure to heat, oil and chemicals. The unique properties attributed to it have resulted in wide adoption of HNBR in automotive, industrial, and assorted, performance-demanding applications. This Practical Guide covers everything from the manufacture of HNBR to processing in the finished part production facility. This book forms a complete guide for the practising rubber formulator or process engineer dealing with HNBR technology
